GulfTalent.com
Tender and Contracts Manager
Morgan McKinley
Dubai, UAE
Posted on: 6 May 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
Morgan McKinley is currently working with an Construction and Engineering company who is seeking a Tender and Contracts Manager to develop and manage the Tender Process and Contract Management Systems.
The role is focused on providing support and input in the development and implementation of business strategy and management of all Contracts.
REQUIREMENTS
The Tender and Contracts Manager will be responsible for establishing strategic tendering, commercial analysis and contract management
processes.
The role will include monitoring these processes to ensure ongoing compliance with the company’s internal policies and procedures.
Essential:
•Minimum 7 years Contract Management or Business Management within the offshore oil and gas industry
•Law degree / qualification a plus
•Cost-estimation, tendering and project experience
•Able to train Tender and Contracts teams and ensure succession planning processes are in place
Skills:
•Excellent communication, negotiation, problem solving and decision making skills
•Apply effective communication and motivational techniques in supervising subordinates
•Good knowledge of contract law, liability and insurance provisions
ABOUT THE COMPANY
In November 2010, GCC specialist recruiter, iQ selection came together with global professional recruitment consultancy Morgan McKinley, under the name Morgan McKinley.
With 24 offices globally, Morgan McKinley connects specialist talent with leading employers across multiple industries and disciplines. We work very closely with international corporates, top investment banks and local SMEs to provide those looking for their next career move with the best job opportunities.
From our Dubai office, we provide specialist recruitment expertise spanning Financial Services & Finance; Sales, Marketing & Support; and Technical sectors throughout the GCC region, with dedicated consultants delivering focused sector and local knowledge. In addition, we are fully committed to promoting the government’s Emiratisation policy.
